WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:12.000
Domino's. Quick starter. Troy. Retold by Bill Bowler. Red by Danica Fairman. Hugh Kermode.

00:12.000 --> 00:22.000
Nick Mercer. Chris Mills. Claire Morgan. Jane Whittenshaw. And James Daniel Wilson.

00:22.000 --> 00:26.000
Published in Copyright Oxford University Press 2013.

00:52.000 --> 01:06.000
One begins when Priam is the king of Troy, and Hecuba is his queen. At first, things go well for them.

01:06.000 --> 01:18.000
They have a daughter, Cassandra, and later a son, Hector. Then, after some more years,

01:18.000 --> 01:32.000
they have a second son. His name is Paris. But when this child arrives, Hecuba is not happy.

01:32.000 --> 01:40.000
What's wrong? Priam asks. I'm afraid. Hecuba answers.

01:40.000 --> 01:49.000
I see Troy in flames years from now, because Paris brings disaster to us.

01:49.000 --> 02:01.000
Priam takes away his young son fast. He speaks quietly to one of his men, Agileus.

02:02.000 --> 02:09.000
Take this child into the mountains. He must die there.

02:09.000 --> 02:19.000
So, Agileus takes Paris to Mount Ida. But he cannot kill the young boy there.

02:19.000 --> 02:25.000
You can live here with me and help with the sheep when you're older.

02:25.000 --> 02:33.000
Agileus says. He gives the child to one of the women in his country house.

02:33.000 --> 02:44.000
Then he goes back to Troy. He gives a dead dog's heart to Priam and says,

02:44.000 --> 02:55.000
My king, your son is dead. He is his heart. Good work, Agileus.

02:55.000 --> 02:58.000
Priam smiles.

02:58.000 --> 03:16.000
Chapter 2 The Golden Apple

03:28.000 --> 03:45.000
So, Paris lives on Mount Ida. When he is young, he helps with Agileus' sheep.

03:45.000 --> 03:55.000
He is a wonderful shepherd boy. And he's very honest too. Agileus says.

03:55.000 --> 04:07.000
Soon, everybody in the country knows about Agileus' son, the honest young shepherd.

04:07.000 --> 04:16.000
In Greece at the same time, King Peleus of Thessaly is happy.

04:16.000 --> 04:23.000
He asks the gods and goddesses from Mount Olympus to his house.

04:23.000 --> 04:32.000
Why? Because he is marrying Thetus, a young sea goddess.

04:32.000 --> 04:42.000
Peleus asks all the gods to the wedding. But he forgets one of the goddesses.

04:42.000 --> 04:51.000
Her name is Eris. She is the goddess of disagreements.

04:51.000 --> 05:02.000
After the wedding, Peleus, Thetus and the gods and goddesses sit at a long table.

05:02.000 --> 05:07.000
I'm hungry. Let's eat.

05:07.000 --> 05:18.000
Zeus, the king of Olympus, says to everyone there. Just then, Eris arrives.

05:18.000 --> 05:24.000
Goddesses, here's something for you.

05:24.000 --> 05:38.000
She cries. She quickly puts a golden apple on the table. Then, with an angry laugh, she leaves.

05:38.000 --> 05:45.000
Here, the queen of Olympus takes the apple in her hand.

05:45.000 --> 05:51.000
I can read something on it. She says.

05:51.000 --> 05:58.000
What? Aphrodite, the love goddess asks.

05:58.000 --> 06:07.000
Here, Eris looks at it carefully. For the most beautiful, she reads.

06:07.000 --> 06:10.000
But who's that?

06:10.000 --> 06:14.000
Athena, Zeus' daughter asks.

06:14.000 --> 06:23.000
Let's ask Zeus. Here are laughs. She quickly gives the golden apple to him.

06:23.000 --> 06:27.000
Hmm. I can't say.

06:27.000 --> 06:30.000
Zeus answers.

06:30.000 --> 06:37.000
We need help from an honest man, I think. Listen.

06:37.000 --> 06:40.000
Hermes cries.

06:40.000 --> 06:50.000
There's a very honest young shepherd on Mount Ida. Let's ask him.

06:50.000 --> 06:51.000
All right?

06:51.000 --> 06:59.000
Zeus says. He puts the golden apple in the messenger god's hand.

06:59.000 --> 07:09.000
At once, Hermes takes the goddesses Hera, Athena and Aphrodite to Mount Ida.

07:09.000 --> 07:25.000
Chapter 3

07:25.000 --> 07:30.000
Who is the best?

07:31.000 --> 07:52.000
Soon, Hermes and the goddesses meet Paris.

07:52.000 --> 07:58.000
Hermes gives Eris' apple to the young shepherd.

07:58.000 --> 08:02.000
He tells Paris all about it.

08:02.000 --> 08:13.000
Now look and please tell us. Who is the most beautiful goddess of them all?

08:13.000 --> 08:18.000
He says. The three goddesses smile at Paris.

08:19.000 --> 08:28.000
Choose me, Hera says. And you can be a great king of many countries.

08:28.000 --> 08:33.000
Choose me. Athena tells him.

08:33.000 --> 08:39.000
And you can win all fights and learn great things.

08:39.000 --> 08:44.000
Choose me, Aphrodite calls.

08:44.000 --> 08:49.000
And you can marry the most beautiful woman.

08:49.000 --> 08:54.000
Paris gives the apple to Aphrodite.

08:54.000 --> 09:03.000
At once, Hermes and the three goddesses leave for Mount Olympus.

09:03.000 --> 09:11.000
Not long after that, one of King Priam's messengers visits Mount Ida.

09:11.000 --> 09:16.000
Priam calls all the young men in the country to Troy.

09:16.000 --> 09:21.000
He tells Paris. Why?

09:21.000 --> 09:24.000
The young shepherd asks.

09:24.000 --> 09:27.000
For the Trojan games.

09:27.000 --> 09:30.000
The messenger answers.

09:30.000 --> 09:38.000
So Paris says goodbye to Agileus and goes to Troy.

09:38.000 --> 09:43.000
But the old man goes after him.

09:43.000 --> 09:47.000
Paris runs very fast and well.

09:47.000 --> 09:53.000
He is the best runner in the Trojan games.

09:53.000 --> 09:58.000
King Priam gives the first prize to him.

09:58.000 --> 10:00.000
What's your name?

10:00.000 --> 10:03.000
The king asks.

10:03.000 --> 10:05.000
I'm Paris.

10:05.000 --> 10:08.000
The young shepherd answers.

10:08.000 --> 10:11.000
And I come from Mount Ida.

10:11.000 --> 10:17.000
Priam suddenly looks at him differently.

10:17.000 --> 10:21.000
Are you my son?

10:21.000 --> 10:24.000
He asks.

10:24.000 --> 10:27.000
Agileus is standing near them.

10:27.000 --> 10:33.000
He quickly tells the king everything.

10:33.000 --> 10:38.000
Priam is very sorry for his past deeds.

10:38.000 --> 10:44.000
So he is not angry with Agileus.

10:44.000 --> 10:49.000
Paris, my boy, you're alive.

10:49.000 --> 10:52.000
He cries happily.

10:52.000 --> 10:56.000
You must come home with me.

10:56.000 --> 11:00.000
So Paris goes and lives in Troy.

11:00.000 --> 11:07.000
With Priam, Hecuba, Cassandra and Hector.

11:07.000 --> 11:11.000
Then one day, Priam says...

11:11.000 --> 11:16.000
Son, you must go at once to Sparta in Greece.

11:16.000 --> 11:22.000
You must visit the Spartan king. Menelaus for me.

11:26.000 --> 11:32.000
Chapter 4.

11:32.000 --> 11:41.000
Love is beautiful.

11:56.000 --> 12:05.000
Paris goes across the sea to Sparta.

12:05.000 --> 12:10.000
But old king Menelaus is not there.

12:10.000 --> 12:12.000
He's in my senai.

12:12.000 --> 12:16.000
His young queen Helen says...

12:16.000 --> 12:20.000
He's visiting his brother Agamemnon there.

12:20.000 --> 12:25.000
Agamemnon is the greatest of all the Greek kings.

12:25.000 --> 12:30.000
But please stay here and talk with me.

12:30.000 --> 12:33.000
Helen is very beautiful.

12:33.000 --> 12:37.000
So Paris stays.

12:37.000 --> 12:41.000
At the same time in Thessaly,

12:41.000 --> 12:46.000
King Paleus and Queen Thetis have a son.

12:46.000 --> 12:51.000
His name is Achilles.

12:51.000 --> 12:55.000
An old priestess tells Thetis...

12:55.000 --> 12:58.000
You must be careful.

12:58.000 --> 13:05.000
One day, your son Achilles must go and fight in Troy.

13:05.000 --> 13:10.000
And he must die there too.

13:10.000 --> 13:13.000
Thetis is afraid.

13:13.000 --> 13:18.000
She takes Achilles down to the dark river Styx.

13:18.000 --> 13:24.000
Then she takes her son's left heel in her hand.

13:24.000 --> 13:31.000
And she puts him under the water for a minute.

13:31.000 --> 13:37.000
After this, nobody can kill him with a sword.

13:37.000 --> 13:42.000
But his left heel stays weak.

13:42.000 --> 13:48.000
In Sparta, Paris and Helen talk happily.

13:48.000 --> 13:50.000
I love you.

13:50.000 --> 13:52.000
Paris says...

13:52.000 --> 13:54.000
I love you too.

13:54.000 --> 13:57.000
Helen answers.

13:57.000 --> 14:00.000
Then come to Troy and marry me.

14:00.000 --> 14:02.000
Paris cries...

14:02.000 --> 14:04.000
All right.

14:04.000 --> 14:10.000
Helen smiles and she leaves with him.

14:10.000 --> 14:14.000
When Paris brings Helen of Sparta home,

14:14.000 --> 14:18.000
his sister Cassandra is not happy.

14:18.000 --> 14:20.000
Disaster!

14:20.000 --> 14:24.000
Now the Greeks must come for Helen.

14:24.000 --> 14:30.000
I see Troy in flames and all our family dead.

14:30.000 --> 14:36.000
She cries, but nobody listens to her.

14:36.000 --> 14:40.000
Paris marries Helen that afternoon.

14:40.000 --> 14:47.000
From that day, she is Helen of Troy.

14:47.000 --> 14:53.000
When Menelaus comes back from Mycenae to Sparta,

14:53.000 --> 14:56.000
Helen is not at home.

14:56.000 --> 14:58.000
Where's the Queen?

14:58.000 --> 15:00.000
He asks...

15:00.000 --> 15:04.000
He is very angry when he learns.

15:04.000 --> 15:09.000
He goes and tells his brother Agamemnon.

15:09.000 --> 15:12.000
We must fight the Trojans.

15:12.000 --> 15:16.000
Agamemnon cries angrily.

15:16.000 --> 15:20.000
We must bring Helen back.

15:35.000 --> 15:37.000
Chapter 5...

15:37.000 --> 15:40.000
Years of War

15:59.000 --> 16:03.000
The Greek fighters are coming across the sea

16:03.000 --> 16:06.000
in 1000 ships.

16:06.000 --> 16:11.000
The Trojans hear of this and go into Troy.

16:11.000 --> 16:18.000
They close the town gates and wait for war.

16:18.000 --> 16:28.000
After many days at sea, Agamemnon's men arrive on the beaches of Troy.

16:28.000 --> 16:34.000
That night, they sleep in their tents on the beach.

16:34.000 --> 16:44.000
The next day, Menelaus and Odysseus, King of Ithaca, go to the town.

16:44.000 --> 16:48.000
They want to speak to King Priam,

16:48.000 --> 16:54.000
but the Trojans do not open the gates to them.

16:54.000 --> 16:58.000
Priam's messenger tells the Greeks.

16:58.000 --> 17:04.000
Helen of Troy is happy here, so leave us and go home.

17:04.000 --> 17:10.000
Menelaus and Odysseus go to Agamemnon's tent.

17:10.000 --> 17:15.000
They tell the great king everything.

17:15.000 --> 17:18.000
He is very angry.

17:18.000 --> 17:23.000
So the Trojan War begins.

17:23.000 --> 17:28.000
For years, the Trojans stay in their town.

17:28.000 --> 17:31.000
They come out and fight.

17:31.000 --> 17:36.000
Then they go back and sleep.

17:36.000 --> 17:41.000
For years, the Greeks wait on the beaches.

17:41.000 --> 17:49.000
They fight every day, and they eat and drink at night.

17:49.000 --> 17:54.000
After many long years, young men are old.

17:54.000 --> 18:04.000
Boys are now young men, but the Trojan War doesn't stop.

18:04.000 --> 18:11.000
One day, Paris and Menelaus meet in battle.

18:11.000 --> 18:18.000
All the Greek and Trojan fighters watch them.

18:18.000 --> 18:23.000
Paris is weaker than Menelaus, but he is faster.

18:23.000 --> 18:28.000
In the end, Paris is afraid.

18:28.000 --> 18:34.000
He runs away from Menelaus into Troy.

18:34.000 --> 18:41.000
The Greeks laugh at him and call him a weak boy.

18:41.000 --> 18:48.000
After that, Helen stops speaking to him.

18:48.000 --> 18:54.000
Back in Greece, Achilles is now a young man.

18:54.000 --> 19:01.000
With his best friend, Patroclus, he wants to fight the Trojans.

19:01.000 --> 19:09.000
But his mother, Thetis, doesn't want to lose him in the war.

19:09.000 --> 19:29.000
Chapter 6 When Prophecies Come True

19:29.000 --> 19:55.000
On the Trojan beach one day, Odysseus asks a priest,

19:55.000 --> 19:58.000
How can we win this war?

19:58.000 --> 20:01.000
Bring Achilles here.

20:01.000 --> 20:03.000
The priest answers.

20:03.000 --> 20:09.000
So Odysseus goes to Greece for Achilles.

20:09.000 --> 20:17.000
Before Achilles and Patroclus leave for Troy, Thetis arrives.

20:17.000 --> 20:22.000
She gives some golden armor to her son.

20:22.000 --> 20:28.000
At first, Achilles does well in Troy.

20:28.000 --> 20:31.000
He kills many Trojans.

20:31.000 --> 20:37.000
Then he and Agamemnon have a disagreement.

20:37.000 --> 20:47.000
Achilles brings back a Trojan woman from one battle, but Agamemnon takes her.

20:47.000 --> 20:54.000
After that, Achilles stays angrily in his tent.

20:54.000 --> 21:03.000
Under Priam's son, Hector, the Trojans begin winning the war.

21:03.000 --> 21:07.000
So Patroclus visits Achilles.

21:07.000 --> 21:10.000
Please come and fight.

21:10.000 --> 21:13.000
He says, No.

21:13.000 --> 21:20.000
Achilles answers, but he gives his golden armor to his friend.

21:20.000 --> 21:23.000
Patroclus wears it.

21:23.000 --> 21:28.000
In battle, Hector sees the armor.

21:28.000 --> 21:31.000
Hey, Achilles!

21:31.000 --> 21:34.000
He cries angrily.

21:34.000 --> 21:42.000
Hector fights and kills young Patroclus.

21:42.000 --> 21:52.000
After that, Achilles fights and kills Hector.

21:52.000 --> 21:59.000
He takes the Trojan's body back to his tent.

21:59.000 --> 22:03.000
That night, Priam comes.

22:03.000 --> 22:11.000
He asks for Hector's body, but Achilles says no to him.

22:11.000 --> 22:19.000
Days later, the Greeks get in their ships and go.

22:19.000 --> 22:25.000
They leave a big wooden horse on the beach.

22:25.000 --> 22:29.000
What a wonderful horse!

22:29.000 --> 22:32.000
The Trojans cry.

22:32.000 --> 22:38.000
They take it into Troy.

22:38.000 --> 22:44.000
But when the Trojans sleep, the Greek ships come back.

22:44.000 --> 22:51.000
Odysseus and his friends come out of the horse.

22:51.000 --> 22:57.000
They open the town gates to Agamemnon's men.

22:57.000 --> 23:02.000
Soon, Troy is in flames.

23:02.000 --> 23:05.000
Trojans and Greeks fight.

23:06.000 --> 23:11.000
Paris hits Achilles in the heel with one of his arrows.

23:11.000 --> 23:16.000
It poisons Achilles and he dies.

23:16.000 --> 23:22.000
Then the Greeks kill Priam and Paris.

23:22.000 --> 23:32.000
And they find and take Hecuba, Cassandra and Helen.

23:32.000 --> 23:40.000
That night, all the different old prophecies from before come true.

24:03.000 --> 24:08.000
.

24:08.000 --> 24:12.000
.

24:12.000 --> 24:17.000
.

24:17.000 --> 24:22.000
.

24:22.000 --> 24:27.000
.

